g.text: CrypticGuard generates a highly secure
RSA-4096 bit private-public key pair, along
with a symmetric key using the AES-256
encryption algorithm. The private key is
securely stored on your USB drive.
Upon shutdown or reboot, CrypticGuard uses the
AES-256 symmetric key to encrypt files within
your specified directories. By leveraging multi-
threading alongside advanced symmetric
encryption, it ensures efficient file encryption.
The public key is subsequently
used to encrypt the symmetric key.
encrypts
On boot, CrypticGuard retrieves the private key
from your USB drive and uses it to decrypt the
symmetric key. By combining multi-threading with
advanced symmetric encryption, it ensures a fast
and efficient decryption process.
decrypts
The decrypted symmetric key is then
used to unlock and decrypt the files in
your specified directories.
